    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-01-29T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-01-29T18:00:00-05:00" n="122"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d122">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/3697: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul General at Shanghai (<persName corresp="#p_CES1" type="to"
                            >Cunningham</persName>)</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-01-29T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >January 29, 1932—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Tokyo Embassy reports under date of January 29, 5 p.m., that our Naval Attaché at
                    Tokyo had received an official account from the Japanese <pb facs="0205" n="101"
                        xml:id="pg_101"/> Navy Department of events at Shanghai so far. The naval
                    authorities state that the landing of Japanese forces was with an understanding
                    with the Shanghai municipal authorities, “to protect Japanese residents outside
                    of Settlement zone”. Do you know of any such understanding with the municipal
                    authorities?</p>
                <p>Repeat to Legation, Peiping, for its information.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SHL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
